  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I expect my game/app saved data to be still there after closing and reopening the status app\n\nAs a developer, I expect to be able to save my user's data so when the users come back I can let them continue where they left off. \n\nIn the worst case, if status do not want to support saving local storage and cookie across restart, it should disable them entirely so the dapp can explain to the user that data cannot be saved locally\n\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n\n[comment]: # I consider it a bug. Many dapp will require data to be saved locally. For a game it can be the sound preferences but for more complex games it can be a lot more. In case of smart contract enabled dapp, there is often the need to store secret between 2 transactions too.\nThis is what local storage can be used for\n\nBut cookies are also useful for session related stuff.\n\nBoth cookie and local storage get reset upon closing status.im\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\n\n- Open Status\n- navigate to any wesbite that save data to local storage or cookie\n- force close Status\n- Open Status\n- navigate again to the website\n\n### Solution\n- ensure local storage and cookie are saved across restart\n\n(if not possible, it would be better to disable local storage and cookie entirely so the dapp can let the user know that saving data is not possible)\n\n### Additional Information\n* Operating System: Tested only on Android",
